## Who is <YOUR_NAME>
<One or two sentences: your role, main stack, main project(s). Example: "Backend developer building X in Python/TypeScript. Main project: <project-name>.">

## Speed Mode (default)
Code only. Max 2-3 bullets outside code blocks. No WHY/WHEN/THEN unless asked.
- Activate explain mode: type **"explain"** or **"teach me"**
- Return to speed: type **"fast mode"** or **"just the code"**

## Save Rule — ALWAYS
When you tell the agent anything new, it should save it to the vault immediately. It should never just say "I'll remember that."

**Save in a way useful to future sessions** — structured memory files, not daily logs. Update existing files before creating new ones. Keep entries rule-shaped: what / avoid / why.

| What you learned | Save here |
|---|---|
| Domain fix / framework rule | `brain-sync` → `<Domain>-Mistakes.md` |
| General code fix (Python/JS/Bash) | `brain-sync` → `General-Mistakes.md` |
| User preference / behavior | `core.md` (this file) |
| Alias / tooling / CLI | `tooling.md` |
| Project-specific update | `session_<project>.md` |
| General coding rules | `session_general.md` |
| New agent rule | `AGENTS.md` |
| Session summary (human only) | `Personal/Daily-Logs/YYYY-MM-DD.md` |

## Workflow Preference — (example entry)
<Describe a real preference here once you have one, in this shape:>
**What:** one-line statement of the preference/rule.
**Why:** what confirmed it (a specific session/decision), so it doesn't get silently overwritten later.
**How to apply:** the concrete behavior change for future sessions.
